The paper deals with secure transmission in a network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of jamming signals, which falls under the category of network intrusion detection and prevention (cs.NI). The proposed power allocation strategy involves optimization, which is a common theme in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the extension of the proposed system model to multiple relays and Willies, which involves multiple access communication (cs.MM).
